{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.17",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 17 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:1",
      "text": "The Lord created man of the earth, and turned him into it again.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:2",
      "text": "He gave them few days, and a short time, and power also over the things therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:3",
      "text": "He endued them with strength by themselves, and made them according to his image,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:4",
      "text": "and put the fear of man upon all flesh, and gave him dominion over beasts and fowls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:6",
      "text": "Counsel, and a tongue, and eyes, ears, and a heart, gave he them to understand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:7",
      "text": "Withal he filled them with the knowledge of understanding, and shewed them good and evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:8",
      "text": "He set his eye upon their hearts, that he might shew them the greatness of his works;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:10",
      "text": "and they shall praise his holy name, that they may search out his marvellous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:11",
      "text": "Beside this he gave them knowledge, and the law of life for an heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:12",
      "text": "He made an everlasting covenant with them, and shewed them his judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:13",
      "text": "Their eyes saw the majesty of his glory, and their ears heard his glorious voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:14",
      "text": "And he said unto them, Beware of all unrighteousness; and he gave every man commandment concerning his neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:15",
      "text": "Their ways are ever before him, and shall not be hid from his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:17",
      "text": "For in the division of the nations of the whole earth he set a ruler over every people; but Israel is the Lord's portion:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:19",
      "text": "Therefore all their works are as the sun before him, and his eyes are continually upon their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:20",
      "text": "None of their unrighteous deeds are hid from him, but all their sins are before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:22",
      "text": "The alms of a man is as a signet with him, and he will keep the good deeds of man as the apple of the eye, and give repentance to his sons and daughters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:23",
      "text": "Afterwards he will rise up and reward them, and render their recompence upon their heads.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:24",
      "text": "But unto them that repent, he granted them return, and comforted those that failed in patience.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:25",
      "text": "Return unto the Lord, and forsake thy sins, make thy prayer before his face, and offend less.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:26",
      "text": "Turn again to the most High, and turn away from iniquity: for he will lead thee out of darkness into the light of health, and hate thou abomination vehemently.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:27",
      "text": "Who shall praise the most High in the grave, instead of them which live and give thanks?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:28",
      "text": "Thanksgiving perisheth from the dead, as from one that is not: the living and sound in heart shall praise the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:29",
      "text": "How great is the lovingkindness of the Lord our God, and his compassion unto such as turn unto him in holiness!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:30",
      "text": "For all things cannot be in men, because the son of man is not immortal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:31",
      "text": "What is brighter than the sun? yet the light thereof faileth: and flesh and blood will imagine evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.17.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:32",
      "text": "He vieweth the power of the height of heaven; and all men are but earth and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
